SPAN 4397 - Senior Seminar
Required of all Spanish majors. The topic will vary each time the course
is taught and will be announced in advance of each offering. Readings
will vary accordingly. In addition to the particular topic being taught, and
as a requirement of the course, the student will be expected to complete
a senior paper or project related to the course topic and designed in
consultation with the instructor. Papers/projects will be presented by the
students in a colloquium to be held at the end of the term.
